  "body": "#### System information\r\nGeth version: 1.9.10\r\nOS & Version: Windows/Linux/OSX\r\nCommit hash : 8045504abf64a865be4b1dbc780b796a9f5d11cc\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nA possible double lock in func `AddChildIndexer()` in core/chain_indexer.go.\r\nIn `func (c *ChainIndexer) AddChildIndexer(indexer *ChainIndexer)`,\r\nif c == indexer, then a double lock happens.\r\nThe first lock:\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/18213281627b310ac68d22bca7c401ab5f67e1da/core/chain_indexer.go#L441-L443\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/18213281627b310ac68d22bca7c401ab5f67e1da/core/chain_indexer.go#L455\r\nThe second lock:\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/18213281627b310ac68d22bca7c401ab5f67e1da/core/chain_indexer.go#L240-L242\r\nIf that is the case, then\r\nDouble lock also happens in\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/18213281627b310ac68d22bca7c401ab5f67e1da/core/chain_indexer.go#L345\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/18213281627b310ac68d22bca7c401ab5f67e1da/core/chain_indexer.go#L358\r\nAnd happens in \r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/18213281627b310ac68d22bca7c401ab5f67e1da/core/chain_indexer.go#L241\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/18213281627b310ac68d22bca7c401ab5f67e1da/core/chain_indexer.go#L268\r\nTo avoid the bug, we just need to guarantee that a ChainIndexer is not the same as its Child.\r\nOr else, we need to handle the double lock when they are the same.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nNo, I found it through static analysis.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nNo.\r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\nNo.\r\n",
